
[1]whin-stone

   WHIN-STONE, n. [whin and stone.] Whin-stone or whin is a provincial
   name given to basaltic rocks, and applied by miners to any kind of dark
   colored and hard unstratified rock which resists the point of the pick.
   Veins of dark basalt or green-stone, are frequently called whin-dykes.
